sentences: Bridget Kearney (born June 10, 1985) is an American musician and songwriter.
She is a founding member of the band Lake Street Dive and winner of the 2005 John Lennon Songwriting Contest in the Jazz category.
Kearney's debut solo album, Won't Let You Down, was released by Signature Sounds Recordings in 2017.
Kearney was born in 1985 and grew up in Iowa City, Iowa.

Although already an accomplished and devoted double bass player at a young age, Kearney's knowledge, skills and innate capacity for creativity took her to a much higher musical level while studying with Mark Urness, a versatile bassist, composer, and educator in Iowa City at the time who now teaches at Lawrence University in Wisconsin.
Kearney is a member of Lake Street Dive, which started touring in 2007.
